terminology
--------
concepts I'm going to use in this report:
  trigger: write-only controls which stick to a base value and writing
    a different value carries out some action (such as reset to defaults)
  setting: read-write controls which generally return the last value
    written when read (except for margins/redirecting invalid input)
    these generally map to a monitor parameter such as brightness
  osd control: an option available through the osd menu or otherwise
    using the buttons on the monitor
  osd path: names of submenus and options in the osd menu that should
    be chosen to access an osd control, separated by slashes
    (such as: color/color tone/warm)
  persistent: a setting which keeps its value when the monitor is turned
    successively off and on (using the soft-off button on the front
    panel of the monitor)
  transient: in contrast to persistent, a setting which resets to a
    default value after an off+on combination (i.e. is volatile)
    interestingly, this usually occurs when switching on, not off
    (the monitor can also be queried when in soft-off)
  regular: if used alone, acts as transient (i.e. effects are restored
    during off+on), but if 0xb0/1 (store settings) is called after it,
    but before turning off (or on, I don't know), the new value is saved
    and is restored after an off+on combination
  IR: "Invalid response, first byte is 0x51, should be 0x6e"
    error message, which occurs quite often (so seems valid)
    (mentioned in results above)
  OK: the specified control needs no change
  FIX: needs a minor change in the xml file
  TODO: something more needs to be done

